HEADWORD: curettement
<hw>curettement</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>surgery to remove tissue or
growths from a bodily cavity (as the uterus) by scraping with a
curette.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> curettage.</syn>⟦br⟧
